<h2 id='concept-class'>Concept class</h2><h2 id='overview'>Overview</h2>
<ul>
<li>The concept&#39;s class provides a useful way to narrow down the scope of the information that the concept is intended to capture.</li>
<li>In this way, the class is helpful for data extraction. This classification details how a concept will be represented (i.e. as a question or an answer) when the information is stored.</li>
<li>OpenMRS contains several default classes to use when defining concepts, but implementation sites may also create additional custom concept classes for use.</li>
<li>examples of some concept classes are Procedure: describes a clinical procedure, diagnosis:conclusion drawn through findings e.t.c</li>
</ul>
